com.bigdata.rdf.graph

Interface IPredecessor<VS,ES,ST>


  • public interface IPredecessor<VS,ES,ST>
    A interface for IGASPrograms that compute paths and track a predecessor relationship among the visited vertices. This interface can be used to eliminate vertices from the visited set that are not on a path to a set of specified target vertices.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void prunePaths(IGASContext<VS,ES,ST> ctx, Value[] targetVertices)
      Remove any vertices from the visited set that do not line on path that leads to at least one of the target vertices.
